items.label: DCMI Metadata Terms in the /terms/ namespace
Title
items.comment: A name given to the resource.

items.label: Creator
items.comment: An entity primarily responsible for making the resource.
items.description: Examples of a Creator include a person, an organization, or a service.

items.label: Subject
items.comment: The topic of the resource.
items.description: Typically, the subject will be represented using keywords, key phrases, or classification codes. Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary. To describe the spatial or temporal topic of the resource, use the Coverage element.
items.note: This term is intended to be used with non-literal values as defined in the DCMI Abstract Model (http://dublincore.org/documents/abstract-model/).  As of December 2007, the DCMI Usage Board is seeking a way to express this intention with a formal range declaration.

items.label: Description
items.comment: An account of the resource.
items.description: Description may include but is not limited to: an abstract, a table of contents, a graphical representation, or a free-text account of the resource.

items.label: Publisher
items.comment: An entity responsible for making the resource available.
items.description: Examples of a Publisher include a person, an organization, or a service.

items.label: Contributor
items.comment: An entity responsible for making contributions to the resource.
items.description: Examples of a Contributor include a person, an organization, or a service.

items.label: Date
items.comment: A point or period of time associated with an event in the lifecycle of the resource.
items.description: Date may be used to express temporal information at any level of granularity.  Recommended best practice is to use an encoding scheme, such as the W3CDTF profile of ISO 8601 [W3CDTF].

items.label: Type
items.comment: The nature or genre of the resource.
items.description: Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary such as the DCMI Type Vocabulary [DCMITYPE]. To describe the file format, physical medium, or dimensions of the resource, use the Format element.

items.label: Format
items.comment: The file format, physical medium, or dimensions of the resource.
items.description: Examples of dimensions include size and duration. Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary such as the list of Internet Media Types [MIME].

items.label: Identifier
items.comment: An unambiguous reference to the resource within a given context.
items.description: Recommended best practice is to identify the resource by means of a string conforming to a formal identification system.

items.label: Source
items.comment: A related resource from which the described resource is derived.
items.description: The described resource may be derived from the related resource in whole or in part. Recommended best practice is to identify the related resource by means of a string conforming to a formal identification system.
items.note: This term is intended to be used with non-literal values as defined in the DCMI Abstract Model (http://dublincore.org/documents/abstract-model/).  As of December 2007, the DCMI Usage Board is seeking a way to express this intention with a formal range declaration.

items.label: Language
items.comment: A language of the resource.
items.description: Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary such as RFC 4646 [RFC4646].

items.label: Relation
items.comment: A related resource.
items.description: Recommended best practice is to identify the related resource by means of a string conforming to a formal identification system.
items.note: This term is intended to be used with non-literal values as defined in the DCMI Abstract Model (http://dublincore.org/documents/abstract-model/).  As of December 2007, the DCMI Usage Board is seeking a way to express this intention with a formal range declaration.

items.label: Coverage
items.comment: The spatial or temporal topic of the resource, the spatial applicability of the resource, or the jurisdiction under which the resource is relevant.
items.description: Spatial topic and spatial applicability may be a named place or a location specified by its geographic coordinates. Temporal topic may be a named period, date, or date range. A jurisdiction may be a named administrative entity or a geographic place to which the resource applies. Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary such as the Thesaurus of Geographic Names [TGN]. Where appropriate, named places or time periods can be used in preference to numeric identifiers such as sets of coordinates or date ranges.

items.label: Rights
items.comment: Information about rights held in and over the resource.
items.description: Typically, rights information includes a statement about various property rights associated with the resource, including intellectual property rights.

items.label: Audience
items.comment: A class of entity for whom the resource is intended or useful.

items.label: Alternative Title
items.comment: An alternative name for the resource.
items.description: The distinction between titles and alternative titles is application-specific.

items.label: Table Of Contents
items.comment: A list of subunits of the resource.

items.label: Abstract
items.comment: A summary of the resource.

items.label: Date Created
items.comment: Date of creation of the resource.

items.label: Date Valid
items.comment: Date (often a range) of validity of a resource.

items.label: Date Available
items.comment: Date (often a range) that the resource became or will become available.

items.label: Date Issued
items.comment: Date of formal issuance (e.g., publication) of the resource.

items.label: Date Modified
items.comment: Date on which the resource was changed.

items.label: Extent
items.comment: The size or duration of the resource.

items.label: Medium
items.comment: The material or physical carrier of the resource.

items.label: Is Version Of
items.comment: A related resource of which the described resource is a version, edition, or adaptation.
items.description: Changes in version imply substantive changes in content rather than differences in format.
items.note: This term is intended to be used with non-literal values as defined in the DCMI Abstract Model (http://dublincore.org/documents/abstract-model/).  As of December 2007, the DCMI Usage Board is seeking a way to express this intention with a formal range declaration.

items.label: Has Version
items.comment: A related resource that is a version, edition, or adaptation of the described resource.
items.note: This term is intended to be used with non-literal values as defined in the DCMI Abstract Model (http://dublincore.org/documents/abstract-model/).  As of December 2007, the DCMI Usage Board is seeking a way to express this intention with a formal range declaration.

items.label: Is Replaced By
items.comment: A related resource that supplants, displaces, or supersedes the described resource.
items.note: This term is intended to be used with non-literal values as defined in the DCMI Abstract Model (http://dublincore.org/documents/abstract-model/).  As of December 2007, the DCMI Usage Board is seeking a way to express this intention with a formal range declaration.

items.label: Replaces
items.comment: A related resource that is supplanted, displaced, or superseded by the described resource.
items.note: This term is intended to be used with non-literal values as defined in the DCMI Abstract Model (http://dublincore.org/documents/abstract-model/).  As of December 2007, the DCMI Usage Board is seeking a way to express this intention with a formal range declaration.

items.label: Is Required By
items.comment: A related resource that requires the described resource to support its function, delivery, or coherence.
items.note: This term is intended to be used with non-literal values as defined in the DCMI Abstract Model (http://dublincore.org/documents/abstract-model/).  As of December 2007, the DCMI Usage Board is seeking a way to express this intention with a formal range declaration.

items.label: Requires
items.comment: A related resource that is required by the described resource to support its function, delivery, or coherence.
items.note: This term is intended to be used with non-literal values as defined in the DCMI Abstract Model (http://dublincore.org/documents/abstract-model/).  As of December 2007, the DCMI Usage Board is seeking a way to express this intention with a formal range declaration.

items.label: Is Part Of
items.comment: A related resource in which the described resource is physically or logically included.
items.note: This term is intended to be used with non-literal values as defined in the DCMI Abstract Model (http://dublincore.org/documents/abstract-model/).  As of December 2007, the DCMI Usage Board is seeking a way to express this intention with a formal range declaration.

items.label: Has Part
items.comment: A related resource that is included either physically or logically in the described resource.
items.note: This term is intended to be used with non-literal values as defined in the DCMI Abstract Model (http://dublincore.org/documents/abstract-model/).  As of December 2007, the DCMI Usage Board is seeking a way to express this intention with a formal range declaration.

items.label: Is Referenced By
items.comment: A related resource that references, cites, or otherwise points to the described resource.
items.note: This term is intended to be used with non-literal values as defined in the DCMI Abstract Model (http://dublincore.org/documents/abstract-model/).  As of December 2007, the DCMI Usage Board is seeking a way to express this intention with a formal range declaration.

items.label: References
items.comment: A related resource that is referenced, cited, or otherwise pointed to by the described resource.
items.note: This term is intended to be used with non-literal values as defined in the DCMI Abstract Model (http://dublincore.org/documents/abstract-model/).  As of December 2007, the DCMI Usage Board is seeking a way to express this intention with a formal range declaration.

items.label: Is Format Of
items.comment: A related resource that is substantially the same as the described resource, but in another format.
items.note: This term is intended to be used with non-literal values as defined in the DCMI Abstract Model (http://dublincore.org/documents/abstract-model/).  As of December 2007, the DCMI Usage Board is seeking a way to express this intention with a formal range declaration.

items.label: Has Format
items.comment: A related resource that is substantially the same as the pre-existing described resource, but in another format.
items.note: This term is intended to be used with non-literal values as defined in the DCMI Abstract Model (http://dublincore.org/documents/abstract-model/).  As of December 2007, the DCMI Usage Board is seeking a way to express this intention with a formal range declaration.

items.label: Conforms To
items.comment: An established standard to which the described resource conforms.

items.label: Spatial Coverage
items.comment: Spatial characteristics of the resource.

items.label: Temporal Coverage
items.comment: Temporal characteristics of the resource.

items.label: Mediator
items.comment: An entity that mediates access to the resource and for whom the resource is intended or useful.
items.description: In an educational context, a mediator might be a parent, teacher, teaching assistant, or care-giver.

items.label: Date Accepted
items.comment: Date of acceptance of the resource.
items.description: Examples of resources to which a Date Accepted may be relevant are a thesis (accepted by a university department) or an article (accepted by a journal).

items.label: Date Copyrighted
items.comment: Date of copyright.

items.label: Date Submitted
items.comment: Date of submission of the resource.
items.description: Examples of resources to which a Date Submitted may be relevant are a thesis (submitted to a university department) or an article (submitted to a journal).

items.label: Audience Education Level
items.comment: A class of entity, defined in terms of progression through an educational or training context, for which the described resource is intended.

items.label: Access Rights
items.comment: Information about who can access the resource or an indication of its security status.
items.description: Access Rights may include information regarding access or restrictions based on privacy, security, or other policies.

items.label: Bibliographic Citation
items.comment: A bibliographic reference for the resource.
items.description: Recommended practice is to include sufficient bibliographic detail to identify the resource as unambiguously as possible.

items.label: License
items.comment: A legal document giving official permission to do something with the resource.

items.label: Rights Holder
items.comment: A person or organization owning or managing rights over the resource.

items.label: Provenance
items.comment: A statement of any changes in ownership and custody of the resource since its creation that are significant for its authenticity, integrity, and interpretation.
items.description: The statement may include a description of any changes successive custodians made to the resource.

items.label: Instructional Method
items.comment: A process, used to engender knowledge, attitudes and skills, that the described resource is designed to support.
items.description: Instructional Method will typically include ways of presenting instructional materials or conducting instructional activities, patterns of learner-to-learner and learner-to-instructor interactions, and mechanisms by which group and individual levels of learning are measured.  Instructional methods include all aspects of the instruction and learning processes from planning and implementation through evaluation and feedback.

items.label: Accrual Method
items.comment: The method by which items are added to a collection.

items.label: Accrual Periodicity
items.comment: The frequency with which items are added to a collection.

items.label: Accrual Policy
items.comment: The policy governing the addition of items to a collection.

items.label: Agent
items.comment: A resource that acts or has the power to act.
items.description: Examples of Agent include person, organization, and software agent.

items.label: Agent Class
items.comment: A group of agents.
items.description: Examples of Agent Class include groups seen as classes, such as students, women, charities, lecturers.

items.label: Bibliographic Resource
items.comment: A book, article, or other documentary resource.

items.label: File Format
items.comment: A digital resource format.
items.description: Examples include the formats defined by the list of Internet Media Types.

items.label: Frequency
items.comment: A rate at which something recurs.

items.label: Jurisdiction
items.comment: The extent or range of judicial, law enforcement, or other authority.

items.label: License Document
items.comment: A legal document giving official permission to do something with a Resource.

items.label: Linguistic System
items.comment: A system of signs, symbols, sounds, gestures, or rules used in communication.
items.description: Examples include written, spoken, sign, and computer languages.

items.label: Location
items.comment: A spatial region or named place.

items.label: Location, Period, or Jurisdiction
items.comment: A location, period of time, or jurisdiction.

items.label: Media Type
items.comment: A file format or physical medium.

items.label: Media Type or Extent
items.comment: A media type or extent.

items.label: Method of Instruction
items.comment: A process that is used to engender knowledge, attitudes, and skills.

items.label: Method of Accrual
items.comment: A method by which resources are added to a collection.

items.label: Period of Time
items.comment: An interval of time that is named or defined by its start and end dates.

items.label: Physical Medium
items.comment: A physical material or carrier.
items.description: Examples include paper, canvas, or DVD.

items.label: Physical Resource
items.comment: A material thing.

items.label: Policy
items.comment: A plan or course of action by an authority, intended to influence and determine decisions, actions, and other matters.

items.label: Provenance Statement
items.comment: A statement of any changes in ownership and custody of a resource since its creation that are significant for its authenticity, integrity, and interpretation.

items.label: Rights Statement
items.comment: A statement about the intellectual property rights (IPR) held in or over a Resource, a legal document giving official permission to do something with a resource, or a statement about access rights.

items.label: Size or Duration
items.comment: A dimension or extent, or a time taken to play or execute.
items.description: Examples include a number of pages, a specification of length, width, and breadth, or a period in hours, minutes, and seconds.

items.label: Standard
items.comment: A basis for comparison; a reference point against which other things can be evaluated.

items.label: ISO 639-2
items.comment: The three-letter alphabetic codes listed in ISO639-2 for the representation of names of languages.

items.label: RFC 1766
items.comment: The set of tags, constructed according to RFC 1766, for the identification of languages.

items.label: URI
items.comment: The set of identifiers constructed according to the generic syntax for Uniform Resource Identifiers as specified by the Internet Engineering Task Force.

items.label: DCMI Point
items.comment: The set of points in space defined by their geographic coordinates according to the DCMI Point Encoding Scheme.

items.label: ISO 3166
items.comment: The set of codes listed in ISO 3166-1 for the representation of names of countries.

items.label: DCMI Box
items.comment: The set of regions in space defined by their geographic coordinates according to the DCMI Box Encoding Scheme.

items.label: DCMI Period
items.comment: The set of time intervals defined by their limits according to the DCMI Period Encoding Scheme.

items.label: W3C-DTF
items.comment: The set of dates and times constructed according to the W3C Date and Time Formats Specification.

items.label: RFC 3066
items.comment: The set of tags constructed according to RFC 3066 for the identification of languages.
items.description: RFC 3066 has been obsoleted by RFC 4646.

items.label: RFC 5646
items.comment: The set of tags constructed according to RFC 5646 for the identification of languages.
items.description: RFC 5646 obsoletes RFC 4646.

items.label: RFC 4646
items.comment: The set of tags constructed according to RFC 4646 for the identification of languages.
items.description: RFC 4646 obsoletes RFC 3066.

items.label: ISO 639-3
items.comment: The set of three-letter codes listed in ISO 639-3 for the representation of names of languages.

items.label: LCSH
items.comment: The set of labeled concepts specified by the Library of Congress Subject Headings.

items.label: MeSH
items.comment: The set of labeled concepts specified by the Medical Subject Headings.

items.label: DDC
items.comment: The set of conceptual resources specified by the Dewey Decimal Classification.

items.label: LCC
items.comment: The set of conceptual resources specified by the Library of Congress Classification.

items.label: UDC
items.comment: The set of conceptual resources specified by the Universal Decimal Classification.

items.label: DCMI Type Vocabulary
items.comment: The set of classes specified by the DCMI Type Vocabulary, used to categorize the nature or genre of the resource.

items.label: IMT
items.comment: The set of media types specified by the Internet Assigned Numbers Authority.

items.label: TGN
items.comment: The set of places specified by the Getty Thesaurus of Geographic Names.

items.label: NLM
items.comment: The set of conceptual resources specified by the National Library of Medicine Classification.
